tigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260515T023427-66d7d854/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260515T023427-66d7d854/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"helix-8944c622\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eAdd CRM solution-design worked example artifact\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nCURRENT STATE\u0026#xA;The CRM example frame artifacts already exist under docs/examples/crm/:\u0026#xA;- docs/examples/crm/00-discover/product-vision.md\u0026#xA;- docs/examples/crm/01-frame/prd.md\u0026#xA;- docs/examples/crm/README.md\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The CRM stack is retained in this repository only as a HELIX worked example/demo planning artifact, not as product implementation work. The next useful slice is a design-phase example artifact that demonstrates how HELIX carries framed product intent into solution design.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Create docs/examples/crm/02-design/solution-design.md and update docs/examples/crm/README.md so the CRM worked example has an indexed design artifact. Ground the design in crm.prd, not in hidden assumptions.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The solution design should cover:\u0026#xA;- domain entities and relationships\u0026#xA;- major workflows\u0026#xA;- roles and permissions\u0026#xA;- reporting needs\u0026#xA;- external integrations\u0026#xA;- MVP vs later scope boundaries\u0026#xA;- open decisions that require human judgment or later ADRs\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;Do not create application code, implementation beads, runtime infrastructure, database migrations, or CRM product build tasks in this repository. If the CRM example is pursued beyond example/demo planning, it should move to a dedicated HELIX-managed CRM repository.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. `test -f docs/examples/crm/02-design/solution-design.md` passes.\u0026#xA;2. `rg -n \u0026#34;Domain Entities|Major Workflows|Roles|Permissions|Reporting|External Integrations|MVP|Later|Open Decisions\u0026#34; docs/examples/crm/02-design/solution-design.md` finds the expected design sections.\u0026#xA;3. `rg -n \u0026#34;crm.solution-design|02-design/solution-design.md\u0026#34; docs/examples/crm/README.md` proves the new design artifact is indexed.\u0026#xA;4. `bash tests/validate-context-digests.sh` passes.\u0026#xA;5. `git diff --check` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ehelix, phase:build, kind:doc